    verification d0074CorrectnessCritique : Test { :>> id = "7d007402-0074-4e74-9c74-516273840a02"; :>> title = "Critique d0074 — correctness"; :>> createdAt = "2026-06-21"; :>> createdBy = "claudeOpus"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::critique; :>> lens = CritiqueLens::correctness; :>> critiquedBy = CriticKind::aiModel; :>> procedureText = "ATTACK: is Rust-first + strangler-fig port the right call vs keeping Python? SURVIVED: a single authoritative impl with compile-time + fail-loud lint guarantees beats two drifting ones — the issue012 query.py-vs-rust orient divergence is the cited real warning; the sequenced strangler-fig (vs big-bang) keeps each step green/reviewable; fail-loud (deny unwrap/panic/silent-fallback) extends the loud-validator value to all tooling. Alternatives (permanent Python; big-bang) explicitly weighed + rejected with reasons. Correct."; }
